Categories: Structured Text Processing -> Operation on Primitives -> Numbers -> List
Definition: In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should only return an integer if the first digit is the same as the last digit in the number. If an integer has a single digit, then it should be returned. If there are no integers that start and end with the same digit then an empty list ("[]") should be returned.

Positive Examples.explanation: The integers 77, 999, and 121 are the only integers in the input list that start and end with the same digit.
There are no integers that start and end with the same digit.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output does not include the integer '2'. This integer has a single digit and should be included in the output.
The ouput included integers that had two of the same digit, but the first and last digit were not the same.
